<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF109-609-427  </DOCNO><DOCID>09 609 427.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Telephony  Nov 12 1990 v219 n21 p32(2).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Getting enhanced services without a network overhaul. (telephoneservices)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Hoffman, Phyllis.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Multi-application platforms offer a quick and cost-effective wayto provide enhanced telephone services, demanded by both businessand consumer customers.andP;  Enhanced services - voice mail, forexample - traditionally have been developed as dedicated pieces ofhardware, but as the number of such single-function platforms hasgrown, service providers realize that consolidating services on asingle platform is more efficient.andP;  Technology vendors haveresponded to this market need, so that there is now a selection ofmulti-application platforms that allow for creation of innovativeservices by supplementing, rather than modifying, an existingnetwork.andP;  Service providers and vendors should work together tointegrate multi-application platforms into the existing switchinfrastructure, and technology should be designed to accommodatenew interfaces and standards.andP;  Thus, service providers can fullycapitalize on market opportunities.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     Telephone companiesTelephone systemsCommunications EquipmentCommunications SoftwareProduct Development.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>